// CanBoot default init.cdo
// canboot-init-marker
//
// Loaded by kmain at boot from /init.cdo on the first writable disk,
// falling back to the boot ISO9660 image if no disk carries one.
// Once the CanDo VM is vendored (milestone 9) this file is what the
// vendored interpreter will execute as the userspace entry point.

print("canboot: hello from init.cdo")
